<p>Ask yourself one question. What task do I dread doing every week? Start there.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Choose the Right Tool</h3>
<p>Match the tool to the workflow. For blog content and SEO, you need a service that writes, optimizes, and publishes articles for you. For review management, you need a tool that monitors reviews and generates responses.</p>
<p>The <a href="https://www.sba.gov/business-guide/manage-your-business/ai-small-business">SBA recommends</a> starting with free or low-cost tools to test whether AI adds value before committing to paid plans.</p>
<p>Key criteria for choosing a tool:</p>
<ul>
<li>Does it integrate with your existing systems?</li>
<li>Does it require technical setup or coding?</li>
<li>What is the monthly cost relative to the time saved?</li>
<li>Does it offer a trial period?</li>
</ul>
